{"key":"post-11540146","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11540146</id>\n<content>When you guys mention spawn ratios, you really need to mention what to what.&amp;nbsp; In other words, colonized rye or bird seed to compost, manure, straw etc.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;With straw, you'll use about a 1:10 to 1:20 ratio and it will work great.&amp;nbsp; With compost or manure anywhere from 1:1 to 1:4 is going to usually work well.&amp;nbsp; Various isolates will perform better or worse on different substrates, so what works well with one isolate might not work as well with another.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As a general rule, you're going to get 80% of your total possible harvest from the first two flushes, provided you've kept conditions at optimum.&amp;nbsp; There's a lot to be said for having a fresh substrate prepared in time to replace the previous one after second flush to take the most advantage of fruiting chamber real estate.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11540185</next>\n<prev>11539916</prev>\n<first>11538306</first>\n<last>11542884</last>\n<when>1259386229</when>\n<utime>11/28/09 07:30 AM</utime>\n</post>"}